    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 1/2 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs, then add 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[110ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml] </span><strong>water </strong>and your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add the <strong>cracked black pepper</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, then add any <strong>resting juices</strong> from the plate with the steak and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>peppercorn sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1587400186382-x200.jpg",
